WEBVTT

00:00.645 --> 00:01.889
<i>Previously on</i> Mike & Molly...

00:01.890 --> 00:02.889
This is Frannie.

00:02.890 --> 00:03.889
Former student of mine.

00:03.890 --> 00:05.849
- She's homeless.
- And pregnant.

00:05.850 --> 00:07.440
And she's telling us
how she robs cars.

00:13.140 --> 00:14.439
You're gonna come home with me

00:14.440 --> 00:16.178
and you can stay there
until we figure this out.

00:16.180 --> 00:18.309
God, no, no,
you don't have to do that.

00:18.310 --> 00:19.639
I certainly am not gonna
put you out on the street

00:19.640 --> 00:20.979
to raise a baby.

00:20.980 --> 00:22.479
Oh, I'm-I'm not
keeping the baby.

00:22.480 --> 00:23.769
I'm giving it up.

00:23.770 --> 00:25.019
Oh.

00:25.020 --> 00:26.269
I want it to have a safe home

00:26.270 --> 00:28.559
and a chance at a good life.

00:28.560 --> 00:29.770
I'll take it.

00:31.180 --> 00:32.439
I'll take that baby.

00:34.100 --> 00:35.350
I made a promise to you two.

00:36.270 --> 00:37.939
If you want this baby

00:37.940 --> 00:41.639
half as much as I do, you are...

00:41.640 --> 00:45.269
never gonna forgive yourself
if you keep this promise.

00:45.270 --> 00:46.729
We're still going to adopt.

00:46.730 --> 00:48.099
There's a baby out there

00:48.100 --> 00:49.559
- with our name on it.
- Yeah.

00:49.560 --> 00:51.679
Before you know it, we'll be up
all hours of the night...

00:52.680 --> 00:54.100
...knee-deep in dirty diapers.

00:57.270 --> 00:59.309
The good thing about adoption

00:59.310 --> 01:01.599
is we can all be part
of the picking process.

01:01.600 --> 01:04.349
No we can't. Who said that?

01:04.349 --> 01:07.479
Hey, you always ask my opinion
when we go shoe shopping.

01:07.480 --> 01:09.019
How is this different?

01:09.020 --> 01:12.139
It's a human being.

01:12.140 --> 01:13.889
Exactly.

01:13.890 --> 01:15.487
Non-refundable.

01:17.350 --> 01:18.519
I say we get a Sagittarius baby.

01:18.520 --> 01:19.769
Anything but a Libra.

01:19.770 --> 01:21.769
They're very unreliable.

01:21.770 --> 01:23.229
Wait a minute, you're a Libra.

01:23.230 --> 01:24.939
I guess this is my way of saying

01:24.940 --> 01:26.940
I can't drive you
to the dentist tomorrow.

01:28.180 --> 01:30.679
Hey. None of you
have a say in this, all right?

01:30.680 --> 01:32.349
Molly and I want
another guy in the house.

01:32.350 --> 01:34.229
Preferably a left-handed pitcher

01:34.230 --> 01:36.769
who's got a little movement
on his splitter.

01:36.770 --> 01:39.309
I don't remember
having that conversation.

01:39.310 --> 01:41.980
You said "healthy baby"...
that's where my head went.

01:43.180 --> 01:44.729
This is the color
I was talking about.

01:44.730 --> 01:46.599
- Color for what?
- The baby.

01:46.600 --> 01:50.559
I was thinking we could go
with a nice caramel coffee.

01:50.560 --> 01:52.559
Aw, and he matches the drapes.

01:52.560 --> 01:56.139
Great, so I'll just tell
the people at the adoption agency

01:56.140 --> 01:57.809
that we're looking
for a left-handed,

01:57.810 --> 02:01.479
Sagittarius, baby boy that doesn't
clash with the curtains.

02:01.480 --> 02:03.019
Hey, wait a minute.

02:03.020 --> 02:05.770
A lot of great pitching's been
coming out of Latin America.

02:07.140 --> 02:08.940
That's him right there.

